    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#jmr2012"/>, n. <citedRange>A.13</citedRange> (no image) </bibl>, whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>62.1795.6</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>117200</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    
                    <lb n="1"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#_ιππος" type="patronymic"><seg part="F">ίππου</seg></name></persName> <space quantity="1" unit="character"/>                    
                    <lb n="2"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><rs type="office" key="archisomatophylax"><w part="I" lemma="ἀρχισωματοφύλαξ"><supplied reason="lost" cert="low">ἀρχισωμ</supplied>ατοφύ<space quantity="1" unit="character"/><lb n="3" break="no"/><supplied reason="lost">λα</supplied><gap reason="lost" atLeast="1" atMost="3" unit="character"/></w></rs> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
                    <lb n="3a"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="line"/>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            
                <p><app loc="2"><rdg resp="#jmr2012"><supplied reason="lost">ἀρχισωμ</supplied>ατοφύ<supplied reason="lost">λα</supplied><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></rdg>
                <rdg resp="#jmr2012"><supplied reason="lost">σωμ</supplied>ατοφύ<supplied reason="lost">λα</supplied><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></rdg> 
                    </app></p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Un tel fils de</supplied> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>ippos, <foreign rend="italic">archisomatophylax</foreign> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">So-and-so son of</supplied> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>ippos, <foreign rend="italic">archisomatophylax</foreign> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Il tale figlio di</supplied> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>ippos, <foreign rend="italic">archisomatophylax</foreign><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
            </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>The personal name at the genitive case at l. 1 seems to be the father's name, probably of the donor.</p>
                <p>At line 2, the preserved letters are probably, as suggested by J.M. Reynolds, part of the title 'bodyguard', for which either <foreign xml:lang="grc">σωματοφύλαξ</foreign> or 
                    the upper rank <foreign xml:lang="grc">ἀρχισωματοφύλαξ</foreign> would be possible (the latter already attested at <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr015500</ref>). If so,
                    the inscription might mention honours for a Lagid officer or emanating from him. Anyhow it would reinforce the feeling that the inscription dates before the end of the Hellenistic monarchy in Cyrenaica.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
